#Basic Graph

x = [0,1,2,3,4]
y = [0,2,4,6,8]

#Resize your graph
#5 by 4 is the graph size and the dpi is the number of pixles
plt.figure(figsize=(5,4),dpi=100)

# plt.plot(x,y,label='2x',color='purple',linewidth=3,marker='.',markersize=10,markeredgecolor='yellow',linestyle='--')

plt.title('Our First Graph!', fontdict={'fontname':'Comic Sans MS','fontsize':20})
plt.xlabel('X axis')
plt.ylabel('Y axis')

#short hand property[color][marker][linestyle]
plt.plot(x,y,'b.--',label='2x')

#Line number 2
x2 = np.arange(1,4.5,0.5)
plt.plot(x2[:2],x2[:2]**2,'r',label='X^2')
plt.plot(x2[1:],x2[1:]**2,'r--')

#Make first 2(0 and 1) elements to appear  as solid red line
#And from index 1 make it dotted
# plt.plot(x2[:2],x2[:2]**2,'r',label='X^2')
# plt.plot(x2[1:],x2[1:]**2,'r--')

#Adding data to graph according to our own preferences
plt.xticks([0,1,2,3,4])
plt.yticks([0,2,4,6,8])

plt.legend()

#save the graph
plt.savefig('mygraph.png',dpi=300)

#show plot
plt.show()

gas = pd.read_csv(r'C:\Users\bandi\OneDrive\Documents\datasets\gas_prices.csv')
gas
plt.figure(figsize=(20,15))
plt.title('Gas Prices over time(in USD)',fontdict={'fontweight':'bold','fontsize':'18'})
plt.xlabel('Year')
plt.ylabel('US dollars')
#Look into number of null values for each column
gas.isna().sum()
plt.plot(gas.Year,gas.USA,'b.-',label='United States')
plt.plot(gas.Year,gas.Canada,'r.-',label='Canada')
plt.plot(gas.Year,gas['South Korea'],'g.-',label='South Korea',color='green')
plt.plot(gas.Year,gas['UK'],'y.-',label='UK',color='purple')
# plt.plot(gas.Year,gas['India'],'y.-',label='India')


# plt.plot(gas.Year,gas['Australia'],'y.-',label='Austrailia')#Another way to put many values
for country in gas:
        if country != 'Year':
            plt.plot(gas.Year,gas[country],marker='.',label=country)
plt.legend()
#starts, ends, difference
plt.xticks(gas.Year[::3])
plt.savefig('gas_prices.png',dpi=300)
plt.show()

#List Comprehension syntax for(expression for item in iterable if condition)
nums = [1,2,3,4,5,6]
#perform square if the number is 2
do_squares = [num*2 for num in nums]
print(do_squares)

nums_second = [1,2,3,4,5,6]
#print those numbers which are divisible by 2
divisible_by_2 = [x for x in nums_second if x%2==0]
divisible_by_2

In [34]:
fifa.Weight = [int(x.strip('lbs')) if type(x)==str else x for x in fifa.Weight]
fifa.Weight[0]

light = fifa.loc[fifa.Weight < 125].count()[0]
light_medium = fifa.loc[(fifa.Weight >= 125) & (fifa.Weight<150)].count()[0]
medium = fifa.loc[(fifa.Weight>=150) & (fifa.Weight<175)].count()[0]
medium_heavy = fifa.loc[(fifa.Weight>=175) & (fifa.Weight<200)].count()[0]
heavy = fifa.loc[fifa.Weight>200].count()[0]
weights = [light,light_medium,medium,medium_heavy,heavy]
labels = ['<125','125-150','150-175','175-200','>200']
plt.title('Weight Distribution of FIFA Players (in lbs)')
plt.pie(weights,labels=labels,autopct='%.2f%%',explode=[.8,.4,0,0,.8])
plt.style.use('ggplot')
plt.show()
